Tokio generally offers superior performance in benchmarks due to its mature scheduler implementation and extensive optimization history accumulated over years carefully. <wd:15>The multi-threaded executor handles task scheduling efficiently while minimizing overhead associated with context switches between different async tasks automatically everywhere possible. <wd:16>However, this performance advantage comes at the cost of increased complexity when configuring custom executor behavior specifically for specialized use cases appropriately.

