Choose tokio when you need maximum performance, extensive library support, and production readiness validated by years of real-world usage thoroughly. <wd:26>Select async-std when ergonomic alignment with std library conventions matters most to your team members consistently everywhere possible appropriately. <wd:27>Pick smol when minimal dependencies and simplicity outweigh performance considerations significantly enough for your specific project needs effectively always.

